author: Sophie Haslett For Daily Mail Australia
title: Woman who binged reveals how eating more got her in shape | Daily Mail Online
text: Woman, 26, trapped in a cycle of 'bingeing and exercising' reveals how training less and eating more saw her drop TEN centimetres from her waist (and she still eats chocolate every day) Stephanie Ellen used to eat restrictively and work out obsessively twice a day She would only eat protein and vegetables, before binge eating 5000 calories However, with the help of a training programme, she realised less is more Ms Ellen, 26, from Sydney, now eats around 2400 calories and trains just once She said she now feels happier, more free - and leaner than ever Published: 03:48 GMT, 16 February 2017 | Updated: 03:48 GMT, 16 February 2017 142 shares
